headline: What Analysts Think Is Changing The Story Behind Dollar Tree Today
summary: Dollar Tree's fair value estimate has nudged higher to about $115.27 per share from roughly $107.13, as investors weigh a cleaner post spin structure against a more uncertain macro backdrop. A slightly lower discount rate of around 7.39% versus about 7.47% modestly boosts the present value of projected cash flows, even as revenue growth expectations ease to roughly 6.39% from about 6.44% amid cautious views on lower income consumers.
